<text top="3" left="356" width="98" height="17" font="2"><b>P R O J E C T S</b></text>
<text top="39" left="356" width="37" height="18" font="6"><b>gvim</b></text>
<text top="39" left="694" width="87" height="18" font="4"><a href="https://github.com/ryangerardwilson/gvim">View Project</a></text>
<text top="68" left="356" width="38" height="18" font="6"><b>Why:</b></text>
<text top="68" left="395" width="362" height="18" font="5"> Wanted to make detailed graph- and animation-rich</text>
<text top="90" left="356" width="419" height="18" font="5">notes while relearning calculus without bloated software that</text>
<text top="113" left="356" width="187" height="18" font="5">broke vim muscle memory.</text>
<text top="142" left="356" width="44" height="18" font="6"><b>What:</b></text>
<text top="142" left="400" width="374" height="18" font="5"> GTK4-based graphical note editor that preserves vim</text>
<text top="165" left="356" width="414" height="18" font="5">navigation across document blocks, with graph rendering in</text>
<text top="188" left="356" width="350" height="18" font="5">declarative Python and inline ThreeJS animations.</text>
<text top="228" left="356" width="13" height="18" font="6"><b>ai</b></text>
<text top="228" left="694" width="87" height="18" font="4"><a href="https://github.com/ryangerardwilson/ai">View Project</a></text>
<text top="257" left="356" width="38" height="18" font="6"><b>Why:</b></text>
<text top="257" left="395" width="352" height="18" font="5"> Wanted to study OpenAI's Responses API deeply,</text>
<text top="279" left="356" width="418" height="18" font="5">compare it against Completions, and see whether the whole</text>
<text top="303" left="356" width="355" height="18" font="5">thing could feel right in a pure CLI instead of a TUI.</text>
<text top="332" left="356" width="44" height="18" font="6"><b>What:</b></text>
<text top="332" left="400" width="374" height="18" font="5"> Rebuilt opencode from scratch as a pure CLI with file</text>
<text top="355" left="356" width="422" height="18" font="5">editing, diff auditing, interactive Q&amp;A, repository analysis, Git</text>
<text top="377" left="356" width="419" height="18" font="5">safeguards, sandboxed shell commands, confirmations, and</text>
<text top="401" left="356" width="166" height="18" font="5">secure API key storage.</text>
<text top="440" left="356" width="25" height="18" font="6"><b>xyz</b></text>
<text top="440" left="694" width="87" height="18" font="4"><a href="https://github.com/ryangerardwilson/xyz">View Project</a></text>
<text top="469" left="356" width="38" height="18" font="6"><b>Why:</b></text>
<text top="469" left="395" width="355" height="18" font="5"> Traditional to-dos reward busywork. I wanted work</text>
<text top="492" left="356" width="402" height="18" font="5">captured as JTBD outcomes that surface value, align with</text>
<text top="514" left="356" width="171" height="18" font="5">mission, and compound.</text>
<text top="544" left="356" width="44" height="18" font="6"><b>What:</b></text>
<text top="544" left="400" width="370" height="18" font="5"> Vim-first terminal task tracker that stores JTBDs with</text>
<text top="567" left="356" width="332" height="18" font="5">North Star scores (p/q/r) for values, impact, and</text>
<text top="590" left="356" width="338" height="18" font="5">embodiment. Pure Python with curses plus CSV.</text>
<text top="629" left="356" width="10" height="18" font="6"><b>o</b></text>
<text top="629" left="694" width="87" height="18" font="4"><a href="https://github.com/ryangerardwilson/o">View Project</a></text>
<text top="658" left="356" width="38" height="18" font="6"><b>Why:</b></text>
<text top="658" left="395" width="362" height="18" font="5"> Conventional file managers lean on arrow keys and</text>
<text top="682" left="356" width="418" height="18" font="5">mice. I wanted a full filesystem browser driven only by Vim's</text>
<text top="705" left="356" width="28" height="18" font="5">hjkl.</text>
<text top="734" left="356" width="44" height="18" font="6"><b>What:</b></text>
<text top="734" left="400" width="376" height="18" font="5"> Python curses TUI directory browser with matrix-style</text>
<text top="756" left="356" width="344" height="18" font="5">rain, modal hjkl navigation, yank/cut/paste/delete,</text>
<text top="780" left="356" width="338" height="18" font="5">reveal/picker/save modes, and custom handlers.</text>
